[1] Ecuador
Date: Fri, 3 Mar 2006 09:45:12 -0500 (EST)
From: Alfonso Rodriguez, MD <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Mi Punto.com, Venezuela, 2 Mar 2006 [trans. and edited]
<http://www.mipunto.com/punto_noticias/noticia_medicina.jsp?
tipo=MEDICINA&archivo=060303010717.tlz2omfi.txt>

Ecuador has recorded 1460 cases of dengue thus far in 2006, of which 1430 are
of the classic dengue and 30 [hemorrhagic type], which caused the death of 2
patients, the minister of Health, Iv Zambrano, announced Thursday.�
He also indicated that the sanitary authorities were investigating 17 other
probable cases of dengue hemorrhagic fever [DHF], a viral disease transmitted
by a mosquito that breeds in winter.�
A month ago, the Zambrano [the local newspaper?] reported that 5 people died
because of meningitis and dengue hemorrhagic fever. At that time, a civil
employee indicated that there were 561 cases of classic dengue and 23 of DHF.
The previous Ecuadorian minister of Health, Wellington Sanchez, warned in June
[2005] that about 850 000 Ecuadorians ran the risk of contracting hemorrhagic
dengue. "We have a very high population, nearly 850 000 people, on the coast,
who have had classic dengue in previous years, and that puts them in danger of
contracting [hemorrhagic dengue]," he stated.
--
Alfonso J. Rodriguez Morales, M.D.
<ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
[Map: <http://www.unb.ca/web/transpo/mynet/map_south-america.jpg>. - Mod.JW]
