[4] China (Hong Kong, SAR), imported
Date: Tue, 28 Feb 2006 09:59:06 -0500 (EST)
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: News.gov.hk, Hong Kong, 28 Feb 2006 [edited]
<http://www.news.gov.hk/en/category/healthandcommunity/060228/html/0602>

The Centre for Health Protection has confirmed a Dengue fever case involving a
48-year-old woman living in Sheung Shui, bringing the year's total cases to 4,
all imported.
The patient travelled to Thailand 27-30 Jan 2006, and got a fever, headache, a
rash, and joint and muscle pain on 4 Feb 2006. She was admitted to North
District Hospital on 9 Feb and was discharged 15 Feb 2006. Her home contacts
have no symptoms. [Dengue is not transmitted person-to-person. - Mod.JW]
