[6] Viet Nam
Date: Mon, 27 Feb 2006 17:20:13 -0500 (EST)
From: Nita Madhav <nmadhav@alum.emory.edu> & A-Lan Banks,Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: People's Daily (China), 27 Feb 2006 [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200602/27/eng20060227_246376.html>

Vietnam has so far in 2006 detected 4800 cases of dengue fever infection,
including 2 deaths, a year-on-year rise of 20 percent, according to a local
health agency on Monday.
The cases were detected in 20 cities and provinces nationwide, but most of
them are in southern Ho Chi Minh City, and the southern provinces of Soc
Trang, Dong Thap and Dong Nai, where weather conditions and local people's
habit of storing water in containers near their houses favor the development
of mosquitoes -- the disease's transmitter, said the Preventive Medicine
Department under the Health Ministry.
To minimize the number of new infections, local health workers are encouraging
residents to kill mosquitoes and their larvae more actively.
Vietnam reported 49 400 cases of dengue fever infections including 51
fatalities last year [2005] [CFR of 103 per 100 000 for nationwide], down 32.7
percent and 49.5 percent from the previous years [2003-2004], respectively,
according to the country's General Statistics Office.
--
Nita Madhav, MSPH
Research Analyst
AIR Worldwide
Boston, MA, USA
<nmadhav@alum.emory.edu>
[Note that report [5] above says:
"Last year [2005] more than 44 000 cases of dengue were recorded in the
southern region, and 47 died [a case fatality ratio of 107 per 100 000 for the
southern region]."
& this report [6] says:
"Vietnam reported 49 400 cases of dengue fever infections including 51
fatalities last year [2005] [CFR of 103 per 100 000 for nationwide]."
meaning the vast majority of cases and deaths occurred in the south.
Map <http://yume-dreams.cool.ne.jp/photo/vietnam/hanoi/vietnam_map.jpg>
